Ben's mockup of chartserver graph, to be generated by code.
(See http://code.google.com/apis/chart/)

http://chart.apis.google.com/chart?cht=ls&chs=250x250&chd=t:250,248,246,247,249,248,248,247|248.5,248.3,248.1,248.2,247.8&chds=245,255&chm=D,D38223,1,0,4|o,257689,0,-1,5&chg=0,10&chxt=y&chxr=0,245,255


http://chart.apis.google.com/chart?
# line chart
cht=ls
# chart size
&chs=250x250
# 2 data sets:  raw vals, and moving-average vals
&chd=t:250,248,246,247,249,248,248,247|248.5,248.3,248.1,248.2,247.8
# ...autoscaled to 1-100 range (max/min)
&chds=245,255
# ... with matching y labels
&chxt=y&chxr=0,245,255
# line styles for each dataset
&chm=D,D38223,1,0,4|o,257689,0,-1,5
# background gridlines
&chg=0,10
